## 📡 Communication Protocol

### Bluetooth Commands (Phone → Arduino)

| Command | Format | Description | Example |
|---------|--------|-------------|----------|
| Forward | `FWD` | Move forward at base speed | `FWD` |
| Backward | `BWD` | Move backward at base speed | `BWD` |
| Left | `LEFT` | Turn left (tank turn) | `LEFT` |
| Right | `RIGHT` | Turn right (tank turn) | `RIGHT` |
| Stop | `STOP` | Stop all motors | `STOP` |
| Go to Waypoint | `GOTO:LAT,LON` | Navigate to GPS coordinates | `GOTO:37.7749,-122.4194` |
| Clear Waypoint | `CLEAR` | Cancel autonomous navigation | `CLEAR` |
| Get Position | `POS` | Request current status | `POS` |
| Set Speed | `SPEED:0-255` | Adjust motor speed | `SPEED:200` |

### Status Messages (Arduino → Phone)

| Message Type | Format | Example |
|--------------|--------|----------|
| Ready | `RASCAL:READY` | Sent on startup |
| Waypoint Set | `WAYPOINT:SET` | Confirmation of GOTO command |
| Waypoint Reached | `WAYPOINT:REACHED` | Destination achieved |
| Waypoint Cleared | `WAYPOINT:CLEARED` | Navigation canceled |
| Status Update | `STATUS:MODE\|LAT,LON\|SAT:N\|HDG:DEG\|WP:LAT,LON\|DIST:M` | Sent every 2 seconds |

**Status Update Example:**
```
STATUS:AUTO|37.774929,-122.419416|SAT:8|HDG:245.3|WP:37.775000,-122.420000|DIST:15.7
```

