## 🔋 Power Distribution

### Voltage Levels

```
7.4V Li-Po Battery (2S)
        │
        ├──► Motors (via L298N) [7.4V]
        │
        ├──► Buck Converter #1 → Arduino [5V, 1A]
        │
        └──► Buck Converter #2 → GPS & Bluetooth [5V, 0.5A]
```

### Current Draw Estimates

| Component | Current (mA) | Notes |
|-----------|--------------|--------|
| Arduino Mega | 50-100 | Typical |
| GPS Module | 50-80 | Active tracking |
| Bluetooth | 30-40 | Active connection |
| L298N (idle) | 10 per driver | |
| Motors (each) | 200-300 | At base speed |
| **Total (moving)** | **~1500 mA** | All motors running |

### Battery Life Calculation

```
Battery Capacity: 2200 mAh
Average Current: ~1500 mA (motors running)

Runtime = 2200 / 1500 ≈ 1.5 hours continuous operation

With 50% duty cycle (stop/start delivery pattern):
Effective Runtime ≈ 3 hours
```

